@Jamie 

Arcade games never had a chance to take off here. There were very few places that had arcade games before 1989 (I recall two in the whole of Warsaw, and one was just a local ice cream bar, which had a single arcade cabinet with River Raid). After 1989, when Poland opened up, it was already the age of gaming at home, on computers. So arcade parlors were not a thing in my life.

I played on an Atari 130XE my parents got me in the mid 80s (at exorbitant cost, as most "Western" stuff was then - they made the immense personal financial sacrifice to bring me up in touch with modernity and the West), and then in 1993 I got my first PC. Also, gaming consoles only became popular here ca. 2000, so I'm ignorant of old console games, which pop up in these puzzles so often. I got my own PlayStation as late as 2009. I've never played a single Nintendo game. In fact, I haven't ever seen a Nintendo game with my own eyes, live. The Switch is sold here, obviously, but it does not seem to be popular (maybe because few people had any of the older Nintendo consoles, nostalgia does not fuel sales of the Switch?)

